Third attempt: use manual distance but making distanceVector component possitive.

```
varying vec4 v_fragmentColor;
varying vec2 v_texCoord;

uniform vec2 position;
uniform float lightSize;
uniform float darkness;

void main()
{
    gl_FragColor = vec4(vec3(0,0,0), 1.0);
    
    vec2 distanceVector = abs(gl_FragCoord.xy - position.xy);
    float distanceValue = sqrt(pow(distanceVector.x, 2.0) + pow(distanceVector.y, 2.0));
    
    if (distanceValue < lightSize) {
        gl_FragColor = vec4(vec3(1,0,0), 1.0);
    }
}
```

We thought we had solved the issue with this (we don't know why it failed originally though) because on iOS 8 it worked, but when we tried on iOS 9 it failed in the same way as the original code.


Maybe we are doing something wrong in our shader calculation, but we think it is weird to get different behavior on different devices.
